  "texts": [
    "Unlike simpler regression models in statistics, it is challenging to demonstrate the importance and function of each network node in a DL model.",
    "The highly nonlinear decision boundaries and overparameterized nature of DNNs, which enable them to achieve high prediction accuracy, also make them difficult to characterize [157].",
    "This lack of explainability is a significant obstacle in computational biology, where the trustworthiness of a DL model is essential for sensitive clinical decision-making applications.",
    "It is equally important to understand why a model can make accurate predictions as it is to understand how it makes those predictions in biology.",
    "For instance, in protein function and structure prediction, we must understand the policies controlling a protein's 3D geometry and attributes."
  ],
